
[1]reverberation

   REVERBERA'TION, n.

   The act of driving or sending back; particularly, the act of reflecting
   light and heat or repelling sound. Thus we speak of the reverberation
   of the rays of light from an object, the reverberation of sound in
   echoes, or the reverberation of heat or flame in a furnace.
